CHANGELOG.md
     1‚Üí# Changelog
     2‚Üí
     3‚Üí## 1.21.3
     4‚Üí
     5‚Üí- Outline more initialization in `race`: [#284](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/284),
     6‚Üí  [#285](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/285).
     8‚Üí## 1.21.2
     9‚Üí- Relax success ordering from AcqRel to Release in `race`: [#278](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/278).
    11‚Üí## 1.21.1
    12‚Üí- Reduce MSRV to 1.65: [#277](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/277).
    14‚Üí## 1.21.0
    15‚Üí
    16‚Üí- Outline initialization in `race`: [#273](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/273).
    17‚Üí- Add `OnceNonZereUsize::get_unchecked`: [#274](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/274).
    18‚Üí- Add `OnceBox::clone` and `OnceBox::with_value`: [#275](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/275).
    19‚Üí- Increase MSRV to 1.70
    21‚Üí## 1.20.2
    22‚Üí
    23‚Üí- Remove `portable_atomic` from Cargo.lock if it is not, in fact, used: [#267](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/267)
    24‚Üí  This is a work-around for this cargo bug: https://github.com/rust-lang/cargo/issues/10801.
    26‚Üí## 1.20.1
    27‚Üí
    28‚Üí- Allow using `race` module using just `portable_atomic`, without `critical_section` and provide
    29‚Üí  better error messages on targets without atomic CAS instruction,
    30‚Üí  [#265](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/265).
    32‚Üí## 1.19.0
    33‚Üí
    34‚Üí- Use `portable-atomic` instead of `atomic-polyfill`, [#251](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/251).
    36‚Üí## 1.18.0
    37‚Üí
    38‚Üí- `MSRV` is updated to 1.60.0 to take advantage of `dep:` syntax for cargo features,
    39‚Üí  removing "implementation details" from publicly visible surface.
    41‚Üí## 1.17.2
    42‚Üí
    43‚Üí- Avoid unnecessary synchronization in `Lazy::{force,deref}_mut()`, [#231](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/231).
    45‚Üí## 1.17.1
    46‚Üí
    47‚Üí- Make `OnceRef` implementation compliant with [strict provenance](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/95228).
    49‚Üí## 1.17.0
    50‚Üí
    51‚Üí- Add `race::OnceRef` for storing a `&'a T`.
    53‚Üí## 1.16.0
    54‚Üí
    55‚Üí- Add `no_std` implementation based on `critical-section`,
    56‚Üí  [#195](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/195).
    57‚Üí- Deprecate `atomic-polyfill` feature (use the new `critical-section` instead)
    59‚Üí## 1.15.0
    60‚Üí
    61‚Üí- Increase minimal supported Rust version to 1.56.0.
    62‚Üí- Implement `UnwindSafe` even if the `std` feature is disabled.
    64‚Üí## 1.14.0
    65‚Üí
    66‚Üí- Add extension to `unsync` and `sync` `Lazy` mut API:
    67‚Üí  - `force_mut`
    68‚Üí  - `get_mut`
    71‚Üí## 1.13.1
    72‚Üí
    73‚Üí- Make implementation compliant with [strict provenance](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/95228).
    74‚Üí- Upgrade `atomic-polyfill` to `1.0`
    76‚Üí## 1.13.0
    77‚Üí
    78‚Üí- Add `Lazy::get`, similar to `OnceCell::get`.
    80‚Üí## 1.12.1
    81‚Üí
    82‚Üí- Remove incorrect `debug_assert`.
    84‚Üí## 1.12.0
    85‚Üí
    86‚Üí- Add `OnceCell::wait`, a blocking variant of `get`.
    88‚Üí## 1.11.0
    89‚Üí
    90‚Üí- Add `OnceCell::with_value` to create initialized `OnceCell` in `const` context.
    91‚Üí- Improve `Clone` implementation for `OnceCell`.
    92‚Üí- Rewrite `parking_lot` version on top of `parking_lot_core`, for even smaller cells!
    94‚Üí## 1.10.0
    95‚Üí
    96‚Üí- upgrade `parking_lot` to `0.12.0` (note that this bumps MSRV with `parking_lot` feature enabled to `1.49.0`).
    98‚Üí## 1.9.0
    99‚Üí
   100‚Üí- Added an `atomic-polyfill` optional dependency to compile `race` on platforms without atomics
   102‚Üí## 1.8.0
   103‚Üí
   104‚Üí- Add `try_insert` API -- a version of `set` that returns a reference.
   106‚Üí## 1.7.2
   107‚Üí
   108‚Üí- Improve code size when using parking_lot feature.
   110‚Üí## 1.7.1
   111‚Üí
   112‚Üí- Fix `race::OnceBox<T>` to also impl `Default` even if `T` doesn't impl `Default`.
   114‚Üí## 1.7.0
   115‚Üí
   116‚Üí- Hide the `race` module behind (default) `race` feature.
   117‚Üí  Turns out that adding `race` by default was a breaking change on some platforms without atomics.
   118‚Üí  In this release, we make the module opt-out.
   119‚Üí  Technically, this is a breaking change for those who use `race` with `no_default_features`.
   120‚Üí  Given that the `race` module itself only several days old, the breakage is deemed acceptable.
   122‚Üí## 1.6.0
   123‚Üí
   124‚Üí- Add `Lazy::into_value`
   125‚Üí- Stabilize `once_cell::race` module for "first one wins" no_std-compatible initialization flavor.
   126‚Üí- Migrate from deprecated `compare_and_swap` to `compare_exchange`.
   128‚Üí## 1.5.2
   129‚Üí
   130‚Üí- `OnceBox` API uses `Box<T>`.
   131‚Üí  This a breaking change to unstable API.
   133‚Üí## 1.5.1
   134‚Üí
   135‚Üí- MSRV is increased to `1.36.0`.
   136‚Üí- document `once_cell::race` module.
   137‚Üí- introduce `alloc` feature for `OnceBox`.
   138‚Üí- fix `OnceBox::set`.
   140‚Üí## 1.5.0
   141‚Üí
   142‚Üí- add new `once_cell::race` module for "first one wins" no_std-compatible initialization flavor.
   143‚Üí  The API is provisional, subject to change and is gated by the `unstable` cargo feature.
   145‚Üí## 1.4.1
   146‚Üí
   147‚Üí- upgrade `parking_lot` to `0.11.0`
   148‚Üí- make `sync::OnceCell<T>` pass https://doc.rust-lang.org/nomicon/dropck.html#an-escape-hatch[dropck] with `parking_lot` feature enabled.
   149‚Üí  This fixes a (minor) semver-incompatible changed introduced in `1.4.0`
   151‚Üí## 1.4.0
   152‚Üí
   153‚Üí- upgrade `parking_lot` to `0.10` (note that this bumps MSRV with `parking_lot` feature enabled to `1.36.0`).
   154‚Üí- add `OnceCell::take`.
   155‚Üí- upgrade crossbeam utils (private dependency) to `0.7`.
   157‚Üí## 1.3.1
   158‚Üí
   159‚Üí- remove unnecessary `F: fmt::Debug` bound from `impl fmt::Debug for Lazy<T, F>`.
   161‚Üí## 1.3.0
   162‚Üí
   163‚Üí- `Lazy<T>` now implements `DerefMut`.
   164‚Üí- update implementation according to the latest changes in `std`.
   166‚Üí## 1.2.0
   167‚Üí
   168‚Üí- add `sync::OnceCell::get_unchecked`.
   170‚Üí## 1.1.0
   171‚Üí
   172‚Üí- implement `Default` for `Lazy`: it creates an empty `Lazy<T>` which is initialized with `T::default` on first access.
   173‚Üí- add `OnceCell::get_mut`.
   175‚Üí## 1.0.2
   176‚Üí
   177‚Üí- actually add `#![no_std]` attribute if std feature is not enabled.
   179‚Üí## 1.0.1
   180‚Üí
   181‚Üí- fix unsoundness in `Lazy<T>` if the initializing function panics. Thanks [@xfix](https://github.com/xfix)!
   182‚Üí- implement `RefUnwindSafe` for `Lazy`.
   183‚Üí- share more code between `std` and `parking_lot` implementations.
   184‚Üí- add F.A.Q section to the docs.
   186‚Üí## 1.0.0
   187‚Üí
   188‚Üí- remove `parking_lot` from the list of default features.
   189‚Üí- add `std` default feature. Without `std`, only `unsync` module is supported.
   190‚Üí- implement `Eq` for `OnceCell`.
   191‚Üí- fix wrong `Sync` bound on `sync::Lazy`.
   192‚Üí- run the whole test suite with miri.
   194‚Üí## 0.2.7
   195‚Üí
   196‚Üí- New implementation of `sync::OnceCell` if `parking_lot` feature is disabled.
   197‚Üí  It now employs a hand-rolled variant of `std::sync::Once`.
   198‚Üí- `sync::OnceCell::get_or_try_init` works without `parking_lot` as well!
   199‚Üí- document the effects of `parking_lot` feature: same performance but smaller types.
   201‚Üí## 0.2.6
   202‚Üí
   203‚Üí- Updated `Lazy`'s `Deref` impl to requires only `FnOnce` instead of `Fn`
   205‚Üí## 0.2.5
   206‚Üí
   207‚Üí- `Lazy` requires only `FnOnce` instead of `Fn`
   209‚Üí## 0.2.4
   210‚Üí
   211‚Üí- nicer `fmt::Debug` implementation
   213‚Üí## 0.2.3
   214‚Üí
   215‚Üí- update `parking_lot` to `0.9.0`
   216‚Üí- fix stacked borrows violation in `unsync::OnceCell::get`
   217‚Üí- implement `Clone` for `sync::OnceCell<T> where T: Clone`
   219‚Üí## 0.2.2
   220‚Üí
   221‚Üí- add `OnceCell::into_inner` which consumes a cell and returns an option
   223‚Üí## 0.2.1
   224‚Üí
   225‚Üí- implement `sync::OnceCell::get_or_try_init` if `parking_lot` feature is enabled
   226‚Üí- switch internal `unsafe` implementation of `sync::OnceCell` from `Once` to `Mutex`
   227‚Üí- `sync::OnceCell::get_or_init` is twice as fast if cell is already initialized
   228‚Üí- implement `std::panic::RefUnwindSafe` and `std::panic::UnwindSafe` for `OnceCell`
   229‚Üí- better document behavior around panics
   231‚Üí## 0.2.0
   232‚Üí
   233‚Üí- MSRV is now 1.31.1
   234‚Üí- `Lazy::new` and `OnceCell::new` are now const-fns
