README.md
     8‚Üí# Overview
     9‚Üí
    10‚Üí`once_cell` provides two new cell-like types, `unsync::OnceCell` and `sync::OnceCell`. `OnceCell`
    11‚Üímight store arbitrary non-`Copy` types, can be assigned to at most once and provide direct access
    12‚Üíto the stored contents. In a nutshell, API looks *roughly* like this:
    47‚Üí# Related crates
    48‚Üí
    49‚Üí* [double-checked-cell](https://github.com/niklasf/double-checked-cell)
    50‚Üí* [lazy-init](https://crates.io/crates/lazy-init)
    51‚Üí* [lazycell](https://crates.io/crates/lazycell)
    52‚Üí* [mitochondria](https://crates.io/crates/mitochondria)
    53‚Üí* [lazy_static](https://crates.io/crates/lazy_static)
    54‚Üí* [async_once_cell](https://crates.io/crates/async_once_cell)
    55‚Üí* [generic_once_cell](https://crates.io/crates/generic_once_cell) (bring your own mutex)
